The paper focuses on developing an information processing architecture for end-to-end visual navigation of autonomous systems, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed architecture leverages convolutional neural networks (cs.CV) and uncertainty quantification methods (cs.LG) to support a predictive control algorithm (cs.AI) that can be applied in safety-critical domains (cs.SY).
